---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";

export const meta = {
  title: "ZZZ Tier List: Comprehensive Zenless Zone Zero Agent Guide",
  description: "Discover which Agents dominate the Hollows. Uncover the shifting meta and see where your favorite characters truly rank...",
  category: "guide",
  published: "2026-03-15",
};

const schema = [
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "ZZZ Tier List: Comprehensive Zenless Zone Zero Agent Guide",
    "description": "A comprehensive guide to Zenless Zone Zero (ZZZ) Agents, explaining their roles, team synergies, and providing a dynamic tier list methodology for Hollow exploration.",
    "author": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Siliconbased.dev"
    }
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is a ZZZ tier list?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A ZZZ tier list is a ranking system that categorizes Agents in Zenless Zone Zero based on their combat effectiveness, utility, and overall value in various game modes like Hollow Zero and Shiyu Defense."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How often does the ZZZ tier list update?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The ZZZ tier list typically updates with every major patch (every 6 weeks), when new Agents are introduced, or when significant balance changes affect existing character mechanics."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Do I need S-Tier Agents to clear end-game content in ZZZ?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. While S-Tier Agents make content easier, Zenless Zone Zero heavily rewards player skill, proper dodging/parrying mechanics, and cohesive team synergy. Well-built A-Tier teams can comfortably clear the most challenging Hollows."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Who are the best Stun Agents in Zenless Zone Zero?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The best Stun Agents excel at quickly filling the enemy's Daze meter to trigger Chain Attacks. Characters like Lycaon and Koleda are highly regarded for their immense impact and consistent stunning capabilities."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do Factions affect the ZZZ tier list?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Factions play a crucial role because pairing Agents from the same Faction or Attribute triggers Core Skill Enhancements (passives). This means an objectively lower-tier Agent might perform at a top-tier level when placed in their optimal Faction team."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
];
---
<SiteLayout site="leeroyjenkins" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://leeroyjenkins.quest/zzz-tier-list" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>ZZZ Tier List: Master the Hollows</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">A definitive guide to ranking, evaluating, and mastering Agents in Zenless Zone Zero.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card callout">
      <h3>Key Concept: The Daze Multiplier</h3>
      <p>In Zenless Zone Zero, raw damage isn't everything. The most critical formula for high-level play involves the <strong>Daze Multiplier</strong>. When an enemy's Daze meter reaches 100%, they are stunned. Stunned enemies take significantly increased damage (often starting at 150% and scaling higher with specific Agents). Therefore, a top-tier team <em>must</em> balance Anomaly buildup, raw Attack power, and raw Stun Impact.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Understanding the ZZZ Tier List Methodology</h2>
    <p>Navigating the chaotic streets of New Eridu and diving into the Hollows requires more than just button mashing. Zenless Zone Zero (ZZZ) features a deeply nuanced combat system centered around parries, dodges, Chain Attacks, and Attribute Anomalies. Because of this complexity, constructing a reliable <strong>ZZZ tier list</strong> isn't as simple as comparing raw attack stats.</p>
    <p>A true ZZZ tier list must account for an Agent's role within a squad. The game categorizes characters into specific specialties: Attack, Stun, Anomaly, Support, and Defense. Each of these roles contributes differently to a team's success in high-level content like Shiyu Defense or Hollow Zero.</p>
    <p>When evaluating Agents for this tier list, we look at four primary factors:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Individual Output:</strong> How well does the Agent perform their primary role (e.g., damage per second for Attackers, Daze accumulation speed for Stunners) without relying on external buffs?</li>
      <li><strong>Team Synergy:</strong> How easily can the Agent trigger their Core Skill Enhancements? Agents that fit into multiple strong Faction or Attribute combinations rank higher.</li>
      <li><strong>Ease of Execution:</strong> Does the Agent require complex, frame-perfect combos to achieve maximum output, or do they offer consistent performance with simpler inputs?</li>
      <li><strong>Versatility:</strong> Can the Agent adapt to different enemy types, or are they strictly locked into fighting enemies weak to their specific Attribute (e.g., Ice, Fire, Electric, Physical, Ether)?</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Agent Specialties and Their Roles in the Meta</h2>
    <p>Before diving into specific rankings, it is crucial to understand the foundational pillars of a ZZZ team composition. A standard team consists of three Agents, plus a Bangboo. A hyper-optimized team rarely consists of three Attackers; instead, it relies on a harmonious blend of specialties.</p>

    <h3>The Stunners: The Backbone of the Team</h3>
    <p>Stun Agents are arguably the most critical component of a top-tier team in the current ZZZ meta. Their primary stat is <em>Impact</em>, which determines how quickly they fill an enemy's Daze meter. Once stunned, an enemy is completely immobilized and vulnerable to Chain Attacks—a series of devastating team-up moves that multiply damage.</p>
    <p>Agents like Von Lycaon (Victoria Housekeeping Co.) and Koleda Belobog (Belobog Heavy Industries) frequently sit at the top of the ZZZ tier list because they can trigger this vulnerable state faster than anyone else. A team without a dedicated Stunner often struggles against elite Ethereals and bosses, as they cannot access the massive damage multipliers provided by the Stun state.</p>

    <h3>The Attackers: The Executioners</h3>
    <p>Attack Agents are designed to capitalize on the windows of opportunity created by Stunners. Their kits are heavily weighted toward burst damage and sustained DPS. Characters like Ellen Joe and Zhu Yuan dominate the top tiers because their burst windows align perfectly with the duration of an enemy's Stun phase.</p>
    <p>However, an Attacker's tier placement is heavily dependent on the Stunners and Supports available to them. An S-Tier Attacker without a synergistic Stunner will often underperform compared to an A-Tier Attacker with a perfect supporting cast.</p>

    <h3>The Anomaly Specialists: The Debuffers</h3>
    <p>Anomaly Agents focus on rapidly accumulating Attribute Anomaly buildup on enemies. When an enemy is afflicted with an Anomaly (like Shock, Burn, Freeze, or Corruption), they suffer severe debilitating effects. For example, the 'Shock' anomaly causes enemies to take additional damage when hit, while 'Freeze' shatters for massive burst damage.</p>
    <p>Characters like Grace Howard excel here. Furthermore, applying two different Attribute Anomalies in quick succession triggers <strong>Disorder</strong>, a massive burst of secondary damage. Teams built around Anomaly and Disorder are currently some of the strongest in the game, elevating Anomaly specialists high on the ZZZ tier list.</p>

    <h3>Support and Defense: The Enablers</h3>
    <p>Support Agents provide crucial buffs to the team, such as Energy regeneration, ATK boosts, or enemy defense shredding. Soukaku and Rina are prime examples, offering immense value that scales exponentially with the strength of the Attackers they are buffing. Defense Agents, while slightly more niche, offer shielding and damage mitigation, making them invaluable for players pushing difficult content while under-leveled.</p>

    <h2>Real-World Examples of Top-Tier Synergies</h2>
    <p>To illustrate why synergy matters more than raw individual power in the ZZZ tier list, let's look at a few examples of meta-defining team compositions.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h4>Example 1: The Victoria Housekeeping Freeze Squad</h4>
      <p><strong>Team:</strong> Ellen Joe (Attack/Ice) + Von Lycaon (Stun/Ice) + Soukaku (Support/Ice)</p>
      <p>This is a classic S-Tier team. Lycaon possesses massive Stun capabilities and intrinsically lowers enemy Ice Resistance. Soukaku provides a massive flat ATK buff and further Ice damage amplification. Ellen Joe then takes the field during the Stun window, utilizing both buffs to unleash devastating Ice damage. This team works beautifully because all three characters trigger each other's Core Skill Enhancements through their shared Ice Attribute and Victoria Housekeeping Faction links.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h4>Example 2: The Belobog Disorder Engine</h4>
      <p><strong>Team:</strong> Grace Howard (Anomaly/Electric) + Koleda Belobog (Stun/Fire) + Anton Ivanov (Attack/Electric)</p>
      <p>This team highlights the power of Anomalies. Grace rapidly applies the Shock anomaly. Koleda acts as the Stunner while applying the Burn anomaly. The interplay between Shock and Burn rapidly triggers Disorder, dealing massive burst damage. Anton then steps in as the primary damage dealer, capitalizing on the Shocked enemies, as his kit specifically deals bonus damage to enemies suffering from the Electric anomaly.</p>
    </div>

    <h2>Why the Meta Matters: Practical Implications</h2>
    <p>Understanding the ZZZ tier list isn't just for min-maxers; it has practical implications for how you manage your account resources. Polychromes (the premium currency) and leveling materials are finite. By understanding which characters provide the most long-term value, you can make informed decisions about where to invest your energy.</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Resource Allocation:</strong> Leveling a character to the maximum cap requires millions of Dennies and hundreds of specific promotion materials. You want to ensure you are investing in Agents that will help you clear Shiyu Defense (the primary source of recurring Polychromes).</li>
      <li><strong>Future-Proofing:</strong> Historically, in games of this genre, Support and Stun characters tend to remain relevant longer than pure Attackers. A phenomenal Support Agent will continue to buff new, power-crept Attackers released months down the line. Factoring this into your tier list evaluation helps you build a robust, future-proof roster.</li>
      <li><strong>Drive Disc Farming:</strong> Equipping Agents with the right Drive Discs (gear) takes immense time and luck. Knowing your team's exact roles allows you to farm efficiently—focusing on Impact for your Stunners, Anomaly Proficiency for your Anomaly specialists, and Crit Rate/Damage for your Attackers.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Adapting to the Shifting Tiers</h2>
    <p>It is crucial to remember that a ZZZ tier list is a living document. The introduction of new Bangboos, new Drive Disc sets, or new enemy types in the Hollows can drastically shift the meta overnight. An enemy highly resistant to Ice damage will temporarily lower the value of an Ice-centric team.</p>
    <p>Furthermore, player skill is the ultimate multiplier. A perfectly timed Perfect Dodge or Defensive Assist is worth more than any raw stat. A player deeply familiar with an A-Tier team's rotation and attack rhythms will almost always outperform a player awkwardly mashing buttons with an S-Tier team they don't understand.</p>
    <p>Ultimately, the best approach to the ZZZ tier list is to use it as a foundational guide rather than absolute gospel. Identify the playstyles you enjoy—whether it's the lightning-fast parries of the Cunning Hares, the heavy-hitting industrial might of Belobog Heavy Industries, or the elegant lethality of Victoria Housekeeping—and build your teams around maximizing those specific strengths.</p>

    <p>By focusing on strong synergistic cores, managing your Daze multipliers effectively, and investing your resources wisely, you can conquer the toughest Hollows New Eridu has to offer, regardless of exactly where your favorite Agent falls on a specific tier list.</p>


    <h3>Related Tools & Guides</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Core App Dashboard Guide</li>
        <li>Secret Santa Generator Tool</li>
        <li><a href="/zzz-tier-list">ZZZ Tier List Explained</a></li>
    </ul>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>What is a ZZZ tier list?</summary>
        <p>A ZZZ tier list is a ranking system that categorizes Agents in Zenless Zone Zero based on their combat effectiveness, utility, and overall value in various game modes like Hollow Zero and Shiyu Defense. It helps players determine which characters are currently performing best in the meta.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How often does the ZZZ tier list update?</summary>
        <p>The ZZZ tier list typically updates with every major patch (approximately every 6 weeks), whenever new Agents or Bangboos are introduced, or when significant balance changes affect existing character mechanics and enemy encounters.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do I need S-Tier Agents to clear end-game content in ZZZ?</summary>
        <p>No. While S-Tier Agents make content easier and can clear stages faster, Zenless Zone Zero heavily rewards player skill, proper dodging, parrying mechanics, and cohesive team synergy. Well-built A-Tier teams can comfortably clear the most challenging Hollows.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Who are the best Stun Agents in Zenless Zone Zero?</summary>
        <p>The best Stun Agents excel at quickly filling the enemy's Daze meter to trigger Chain Attacks. Characters like Von Lycaon and Koleda Belobog are highly regarded for their immense impact stats and consistent stunning capabilities.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How do Factions affect the ZZZ tier list?</summary>
        <p>Factions play a crucial role because pairing Agents from the same Faction or Attribute triggers Core Skill Enhancements (powerful passive abilities). This means an objectively lower-tier Agent might perform at a top-tier level when placed in their optimal Faction team alongside synergistic partners.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

  </div>
  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; line-height: 1.6; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }
    .card { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .callout { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-color); padding: 1rem 1.5rem; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; margin: 1.5rem 0; }
    .faq-section { margin-top: 3rem; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; }
    h2 { margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    h3 { margin-top: 2rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    p { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; }
    li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>
